[[!meta title="Platform for Gordian Edenhofer"]]
# Position statement for Gordian Edenhofer

I have been involved in the Free and Open Source Software community for more
than eleven years, primarily through Arch Linux. I am currently part of the
Arch Linux support staff, contribute to the ArchWiki, and maintain packages in
the Arch User Repository.

Open source has also been an important part of my work life. In my previous
life as an academic, I released my research software and associated work
openly, contributed to several open-source projects, including JAX, and served
as a reviewer for the Journal of Open Source Software (JOSS).

Since moving from academia into industry, I have had less opportunity to
contribute code to open-source projects directly. I would therefore like to
contribute more of my time and experience through organizational and
administrative work. Serving on the SPI board seems like a particularly
meaningful way to support the broader open-source ecosystem and the projects
that depend on SPI.
